ploting example

x
## [1]  3  4  5  6  7  8  9 10
x+1 #no assignment
## [1]  4  5  6  7  8  9 10 11
x <- x + 1; # what happens to x?
#The difference bw theese two lines is an important computing concept
# x =x+1, assign a new value from righthandside to the lefthandside.
x;
## [1]  4  5  6  7  8  9 10 11
#self exercises on self-assignment
# .... ... 

y = x+4
#simple plot
plot( y ~ x );

plot( x ~ y )

x = 1:25;
y = x; 
plot( y ~ x, pch=x);
